I keep root memed at almost all times (i mem enstill when root isn't up) because of it's low mana cost.<br>
<br>
If you root a mob, and you are the closest one to the mob, he will attack you.  If you want to drop aggro, back off slightily and he will attack the next closest person.  just tell teh group that you are using root for aggro management, and if they dont' know what you are talking about, explain it to them.  If it is a rogue who can't figure it out, explain it really slowly :P<br>
<br>
Dammur <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaauan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aauan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/12/01 4:32:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best taunt spells for agro maintenance</span><hr size=1> i figured something out in seb awhile back, though it's mana costly. if i cycle through 2-3 set of full stuns, i can hold agro using just taunt the rest of the fight. if i have c2 i can usually keep up with this all day, just don't cast the rest of the fight unless the mob got off me for some reason. with c2 my mana regen standing is faster than mana regen sitting without c2, i got no wis so my mana regens pretty damn fast.<br>
<br>
<br>
---Ariakkas<br>
<br>
